    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-and-pea-sauce-with-fresh-orecchiette/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>bacon lardons</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-and-pea-sauce-with-fresh-orecchiette/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>fresh orecchiette</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook for 4-6 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>orecchiette</strong>, reserving a cup of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-and-pea-sauce-with-fresh-orecchiette/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the orecchiette is cooking, peel and slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>basil</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-and-pea-sauce-with-fresh-orecchiette/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>chopped basil</strong> with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>in a bowl \u2013 this is your <strong>basil oil</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-and-pea-sauce-with-fresh-orecchiette/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the bacon lardons are golden, reduce the heat to medium-high, then add the <strong>sliced garlic </strong>to the pan and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]<strong> </span>flour</strong> to the pan and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[225ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>milk </strong>gradually and whisk for 2 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-and-pea-sauce-with-fresh-orecchiette/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Stir <strong>half</strong> your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> (save the rest for garnish!) into the sauce with the <strong>drained orecchiette</strong>, <strong>blanched peas </strong>and 100ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [130ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml]</span> <strong>reserved starchy pasta water</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up until the pasta is coated in the sauce \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy bacon & pea sauce with fresh orecchiette</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-and-pea-sauce-with-fresh-orecchiette/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy bacon & pea sauce with fresh orecchiette</strong> topped with the<strong> remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Drizzle over the <strong>basil oil</strong> and season with a generous grind of<strong> black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
